   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="TLx-0028_p001.jpg" xml:id="img_0001" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/TLx-0028_p001.jpg"/>
            <p facs="#facs_1_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_1" n="N001"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> + <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">art</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l" n="N002"/>I. <hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Human nature and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">art</rs>.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_2" n="N003"/>A. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Philosophy">Philosophy</rs>, {and} the question of man and the
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_3" n="N004"/>question of <rs type="keyword" ref="#Being">being</rs>.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_4" n="N005"/>B. Expression as an <rs type="keyword" ref="#Ontology">ontological</rs> category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_5" n="N006"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Artistic</rs> expression. Eros and expression.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_6" n="N007"/>I. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_7" n="N008"/>C. Transformation as an anthropological category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_8" n="N009"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Artistic</rs> transformation.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_9" n="N010"/>D. Anticipation as an <rs type="keyword" ref="#Ethics">ethical </rs>category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_10" n="N011"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Artistic</rs> anticipation.
            </p>
            <pb facs="#facs_2" n="TLx-0028_p002.jpg" xml:id="img_0002"/>
            <p facs="#facs_2_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">II.<rs type="keyword" ref="#Culture"> Culture</rs>, <rs type="keyword" ref="#Society">society</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">art</rs></hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_1" n="N002"/>A. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art</rs> and homo Faber (so called pure art)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_2" n="N003"/>B. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art </rs>and knowledge (awareness and emotion)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_3" n="N004"/>C. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art</rs> and<rs type="keyword" ref="#Ethics"> ethics</rs> (The aesthetic and the ethical
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_4" n="N005"/>point of view.)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_5" n="N006"/>II. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_6" n="N007"/>D. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Society">social structures </rs>(Interdependence)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_7" n="N008"/>E. Social <rs type="keyword" ref="#Symbol">symbols</rs> and anticipation.
            </p>
            <pb facs="#facs_3" n="TLx-0028_p003.jpg" xml:id="img_0003"/>
            <p facs="#facs_3_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">III. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art</rs>.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_1" n="N002"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">A. </hi>The first level: <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and expression universally
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_2" n="N003"/>B. The second level: <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Expressionism">expressionistic</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_3" n="N004"/>expression
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_4" n="N005"/>C. The third level. <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> expressed in its <rs type="keyword" ref="#Symbol">symbols</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_5" n="N006"/>III. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_6" n="N007"/>D. The 4 level: <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religious</rs> style and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">religious</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_7" n="N008"/>content. (The cult picture
            </p>
            <pb facs="#facs_4" n="TLx-0028_p004.jpg" xml:id="img_0004"/>
            <p facs="#facs_4_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Intr. Remarks</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_1" n="N002"/>3. The double purpose: a] <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">Art</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_2" n="N003"/>b] <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religious </rs>and<rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts"> artistic</rs> symbols.
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_3" n="N004"/>1. The situation in the National Council and in Union 
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_4" n="N005"/>2. Difference to former lectures: The double purpose
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_5" n="N006"/>4 The infinity of material and the difficulty
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_6" n="N007"/>of choice. (Each evening differently)
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_7" n="N008"/>5. Three types of students a] Those who are interested.
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_8" n="N009"/>b] Those who want to help {and to be helped}. c] Those
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_9" n="N010"/>who work on problems of <rs type="keyword" ref="#Symbol">symbolism </rs>and be helped.
            </p>
            <pb facs="#facs_5" n="TLx-0028_p005.jpg" xml:id="img_0005"/>
            <p facs="#facs_5_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">2</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_1" n="N002"/>(Possibility of a smaller group. - <rs type="person" ref="#tillich_person_id__1923">Hannah</rs>'s guiding trips)
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_2" n="N003"/>6. Today the meaning of <rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">religious</rs> <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">art</rs>. Pictures
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_3" n="N004"/>{at random}.
            </p>
         </div>
